Part of Speech: verb
Definition: 	1. {'main': 'to emit or give off an odor, feeling of smell.'}
	2. {'subordinate': 'To produce sound naturally without apparent effort; flow forth spontaneously and smoothly'}
Synonyms: emanates, emits, exudes
Antonyms: absorbs, releases into the air or environment without effort from within, conceals

